trend_summary: From the earliest to latest frame the landscape stays dominantly rural, adding only scattered houses along existing lanes. A small diagonal airstrip gradually becomes overgrown, while tree cover creeps into former field margins. Farmland patches shift locations but total cultivated area stays similar, keeping overall settlement sparse.
notable_changes: Several new single-family dwellings built along main roads and cul-de-sacs.
Diagonal grass runway shows progressive vegetation encroachment, indicating disuse.
Woodland edges expand into former cropland and along hedgerows.
Minor reconfiguration of pasture and tilled fields, especially in the northwest.
No major new roads; existing network slightly widened or paved.
